Convert Categorical data into integers

In[]:
# Creating a instance of label Encoder.
df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=["sex", "married", "car", "save_act", "current_act", "mortgage", "pep"], drop_first=True)
# Convert the non-binary categorical data into numerical data using label encoder
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
df["region"] = label_encoder.fit_transform(df["region"])

# Correlation between age & income, using scipy     
x = df["age"]
y = df["income"]

r, p = scipy.stats.pearsonr(x, y)
display("Correlation coefficient. A slightly positive correlation between age & income", r)
